en_63399_0	A spectacle of devotional songs, staged by members of the Sri Lanka Armoured Corps (SLAC) at its Modera Rock House Headquarters was opened Wednesday (4) evening by Lieutenant General Mahesh Senanayake, Commander of the Army at the invitation of Major General Sathyapriya Liyanage, Colonel Commandant, SLAC and Commander, Security Forces – West.
en_63399_1	The display of those aesthetic talents, ‘Bethi Gee’ took place as a tribute to the Poson phenomenon which heralded a new culture and civilization for Sri Lankans many centuries ago.
en_63399_2	Each SLAC Battalion presented three songs of Poson significance to the arrangement.
en_63399_3	Lieutenant General Mahesh Senanayake, Commander of the Army on arrival was received by Major General Sathyapriya Liyanage, Colonel Commandant, SLAC.
en_63399_4	Towards the end of the arrangement, Major General Sathyapriya Liyanage, Colonel Commandant, SLAC presented a memento to the Commander of the Army for his gracious presence.
